        scoreYou:
          'This mission has four ways to score points, though they’re staggered based on what battle round it is, so it’s really only two ways to score simultaneously:\n1: Score 10 VP if you control your opponent’s home objective. [Any battle round, end of your turn]\n2: Score 4 VP for each objective you control, excluding home. [1st battle round, end of your turn]\n3: Score 5 VP for each objective you control, excluding home [2nd and 3rd battle rounds, end of your command phase]\n4: Score 6 VP for each objective you control, excluding home. [4th battle round onwards, end of your turn]\nSo we’re standing on objectives! Easy peasy. The thing to remember here, though, is that not only does the amount you score change, when you score the points during the turn changes, too. Let’s take a look at how scoring should fold out:\n• Turn 1 - 12 VP (control 3 at end of turn)\n• Turn 2 - 5 to 10 VP (hold 1 or 2 objectives)\n• Turn 3 - 5 to 10 VP\n• Turn 4 - 12-15 VP\n• Turn 5 - 12-15 VP\nIt’s clear here that turns 1, 4, and 5 are going to be your big scoring turns. If you’re going 1st, you can pretty easily start the game with 12 VP, fall back a little during turns 2 and 3, and then make a big push on 4 and 5 to take advantage of that end-of-turn scoring. It shouldn’t be too hard to get to 45 in this mission, even if you end up going 2nd.',
