        scoreYou:
          'Three ways to score:\n1: Score 2 VP for each objective that is decoyed (+2 if the objective is within the opponent’s territory). [Any battle round, end of your turn]\nDecoy is your standard “do this on a non-home objective” that completes at end of turn. It has unlimited uses, though, so the Disruption player can kinda go hog wild early in the battle. Markers on decoyed objectives are immediately removed if an enemy unit ends a move within range of the objective, so objectives can be scored multiple times per game.\n2: Score 4 VP if you control 1 or more objectives, excluding home. [2nd battle round onwards, end of your command phase, changes to end of your turn in battle round 5]\n3: Score 10 VP if four or more objectives are decoyed [End of battle]\nScoring is hard to predict on this one, but there’s nothing stopping the Disruption player from going all out on T1 to snag a bunch of points:\n• Turn 1 - 8 to 12 VP\n• Turn 2 - 4 to 8 VP\n• Turn 3 - 4 to 8 VP\n• Turn 4 - 4 to 8 VP\n• Turn 5 - 15 VP\nScoring 15 on T5 is probably a lot harder if you went hog wild on T1, but decoying both of the close objectives and the far central on T1 is completely doable. If you want to spend an infiltrating unit to try and get the far expansion on T1, you can, but if you don’t go first, that unit is almost certainly dead as hell. So on the low end, you’re looking at 35 VP, which includes a T5 push to decoy 4 or more objectives.',
